  "texts": [
    "Targeted, model-aware sampling strategies for dataset generation of three-dimensional atomic positions are especially essential for modelling rare events, such as chemical reactions 17, 29.",
    "Active learning (AL) 30 is a class of model-aware algorithms designed to automatically sample, select and label new data with the goal of efficiently generating a diverse and relevant dataset to train a more robust ML model.",
    "AL aims to ameliorate human bias through automating the decision-making process for adding new data to a training dataset.",
    "Recently, AL has been applied to develop numerous MLIPs trained to datasets of atomic positions labelled with energies and atomic forces from expensive QM calculations 17, 19, [31] [32] [33] [34] [35] [36].",
    "To develop a general reactive MLIP with AL, existing methodologies for selecting, labelling and training are relatively straightforward associated with non-equilibrium thermodynamic processes."
